Make the scan WALK stage cooperatively cancellable. Closing the Scan dialog (or clicking Cancel/X) during WALK now stops the walker within one rglob tick instead of waiting for it to exhaust — fixing the user-visible "must close CMD window to stop the scan" symptom, which was the scan QThread being orphaned after the dialog's `wait(3000)` timed out. Adds observability log lines when the close-path `wait()` does time out, so any future cancel-checkpoint gap is diagnosable from the log instead of from the symptom (#491).
